**Under Construction**

The Craigieburn Regional Aquatic & Leisure Centre (SPLASH) is to be completed in late 2017.

The building was recently pressure tested in compliance with ATTMA TSL1 and TSL2 and AS/NZS ISO 9972:2015 by the firm ‘Efficiency Matrix Building Envelope and Air Tightness’

| www.efficiencymatrix.com.au | +61 (03) 9005 7077 |

**Results**

Results Air flow at 50 Pa, Q50 [m&sup3;/h] =79,650

Air changes, n50 =1.68

Equivalent leakage area at 50 Pa [cm&sup2;] = 39,700

Permeability at 50 Pa [m&sup3;/h/m&sup2;] = 4.984 +/-3.7%

These results compare favourably to the target for ATTMA Normal practise for office buildings (5).

Having a well sealed aquatic centre will reduce energy loss and more importantly reduce the risk of condensation (from warm moist air coming into contact with cold surfaces) and the resultant maintenance and corrosion impacts that can result.
